  • Method Details

    • findUser

      HighestValue.HighestValueUser findUser(Product[] products, Cart[] carts, User[] users)
      Finds the user who has the highest value cart among the given arrays of products, carts and users. The time complexity of the algorithm is: O(2n) /////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////// For Product objects - O(n) For Cart objects - O(n) + For ProductsData objects - O(n) For User objects - O(n) Of course, we can immediately accumulate this data in sorted form, and then the speed of the algorithm will increase. However, it is not known how often we will use this algorithm in the case, which is why it is unclear whether this decision makes sense.
      Parameters:
      products - an array of Product objects representing the products in system.
      carts - an array of Cart objects representing the carts to search for
      users - an array of User objects representing the users who own the carts
      Returns:
      a HighestValueUser object containing the User object who owns the highest value cart, and the total value of that cart
